<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; DT 466E, DT 466, 530, 530E, and HT 530 Diesel Engines - Power Cylinders - Recondition
        Cylinder Sleeve - Recondition Cylinder Sleeve Counterbore
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s210010604.1" svcproctype="recondition" graphiccount="5">
        <title>Recondition Cylinder Sleeve Counterbore</title>
        <svcprocinfo id="s210010604.1.1">
            <para>Check crankcase counterbore depth with
                <hotlnk document="eges2101_157.xml" xrefid="t210010605">Cylinder Liner Height Gauge (ZTSE2515A)</hotlnk>
                or
                <hotlnk document="eges2101_157.xml" xrefid="t210010605">Depth Micrometer</hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc id="s210010604.1.2">
            <title>Preparation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Prepare
                    <hotlnk document="eges2101_157.xml" xrefid="t210010605">Counterbore Tool (ZTSE2514)</hotlnk>
                    with appropriate Counter Bore Cutting Head.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The counterbore tool is a low profile tool which can be used in-chassis.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f210010640" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg5/eg5252.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Counterbore Tool</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Counterbore Tool</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Counter Bore Cutting Head</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Washers (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Mounting bolts (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Spacer (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Locking plate (7)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Feeler Gauge</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Preset Counter Bore Cutting Head by placing a 0.20 to 0.25 mm (0.008 to 0.010 in)
                    <hotlnk document="eges2101_157.xml" xrefid="t210010605">Feeler Gauge</hotlnk>
                    on outside of cutter head. Push cutting head out until it touches Feeler Gauge. Lock cutting head in
                    place by tightening locking plate.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f210010641" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg5/eg5253.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Lock cutting head</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install cutter head on Counterbore Tool.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Raise cutter head, pull plunger and lifting handle. Attach Counterbore Tool to
                    crankcase. Tighten mounting bolts finger tight. Torque mounting bolts to 45 N&#183;m (33 lbf&#183;ft).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f210010642" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg5/eg5254.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Position Counterbore Tool</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turn knuckles</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Locking screws</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Mounting bolts (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Spacers (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Washers (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Locking plates (2)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lower cutting head, loosening locking screws on turn knuckles. Pull plunger up to
                    desired height. Tighten turn knuckle in opposite direction and lock in place with locking screws.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Set depth of cut, see "Resurface, Setting Depth with Graduated Marks on Tool" or
                    "Resurface, Setting Depth with Feeler Gauge" in this section.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="s210010604.1.3">
            <title>Resurface, Setting Depth with Graduated Marks on Tool</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen locking screw.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate adjusting nut counterclockwise until nut contacts driver unit housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Back off adjusting nut by amount of cut desired.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Each graduated marking equals 0.025 mm (0.001 in). If 0.050 mm (0.002 in) material will be
                            removed, you must back off adjusting nut two marks.
                        </para>
                        <para>Never attempt to remove more than 0.050 mm (0.002 in) material at any one time.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten adjusting nut lock screw.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="s210010604.1.4">
            <title>Resurface, Setting Depth with Feeler Gauge</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen locking screw.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert appropriate size
                    <hotlnk document="eges2101_157.xml" xrefid="t210010605">Feeler Gauge</hotlnk>
                    0.05 mm (0.002 in.) maximum between upper and lower turn knuckle. Rotate upper turn knuckle until
                    feeler gauge is just held in place.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f210010643" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg5/eg5255.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Set Counterbore Tool</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten locking screw and remove feeler gauge.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="s210010604.1.5">
            <title>Cut Cylinder Sleeve Counterbore</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To avoid possible engine damage and damage to tool, do not rotate Counterbore Tool
                        counterclockwise when cutting tool is in contact with cylinder sleeve counterbore.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotating Counterbore Tool handle smoothly clockwise, cutting cylinder sleeve
                    counterbore. Continue until tool handle turns freely and is bottomed out between adjusting nut and
                    top of tool housing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f210010644" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg5/eg5256.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Cut cylinder sleeve counterbore</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Once counterbore has been resurfaced, remove Counterbore Tool.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean counterbore, measure counterbore depth. See "Measure Cylinder Sleeve Counterbore"
                    in this section.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
